The first generation iPad was revealed by Steve Jobs in April 2010 . 
  It was met with ridicule as experts struggled to see how popular the device would be . 
  Five years on and 225 million iPads have been sold - but sales are down 18 per cent . 
  Industry experts have predicted that the iPad is in danger of losing its popularity . 
  The iPad Air 2 and Mini 3 are the latest models to be released . 
 